# Update Propagation

*What happens when you edit the ConfigMap?* Depends on the projection.

## Env vars — baked in

> `configMapKeyRef` + `envFrom` resolve **once at pod start**. Edit later → **nothing** to running Pods.

Pick up changes → **restart / rollout** (bump a template annotation).

## Volume mounts — live-update

> `tmpfs` files **rewritten within ~1 min** of a change. Container sees new contents **without restarting**.

- **Footgun** — the app must **re-read** the file. Many load once → still using old values.
- Fixes: **watch the file** (inotify), or **rollout on change** (checksum annotation).

## `subPath` gotcha

> **`subPath` mounts do NOT live-update** — separate bind mount. Need both? Mount the whole CM elsewhere.
